HEADWORD: Ultrared
<hw>Ul`tra*red"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>ultra-</ets> + <ets>red</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld>
<def>Situated beyond or below the red rays; <as>as, the
<ex>ultrated</ex> rays of the spectrum, which are less refrangible than
the red</as>.</def><-- now called infrared -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

